    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-11-15T19:07:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-11-15T19:07:00-05:00" n="527"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/11–1551: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the United States Representative on the Palestine Conciliation
                        Commission</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PEE1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Palmer</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Paris</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d527fn1">Drafted by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_LJW1"
                            >Ludlow</persName>, cleared with Mr. <persName corresp="#p_WJA1"
                            >Waldo</persName>, approved for transmission by Mr. <persName
                            corresp="#p_PDH1">Popper</persName>, and signed for the Acting Secretary
                        by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HJD1">Hickerson</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-11-15T19:07:00-05:00"
                            >November 15, 1951—7:07 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Gadel 158. <gloss target="#t_Unpal1">Unpal</gloss> 300. Re <gloss
                        target="#t_Palun1">Palun</gloss> 468, 469.<note n="2" xml:id="d527fn2">Dated
                        November 14 and 15, neither printed, these messages respectively gave the
                        Israeli and Arab Delegations’ statements on the <gloss target="#t_PCC1"
                            >PCC</gloss> proposals (357.AC/11–1451, /11–1551).</note> In view
                    irreconcilable positions parties as demonstrated by statements Israeli and Arab
                    Dels Dept believes conf shld be ended. Accordingly, you shld urge colleagues at
                    mtg Nov 16 advise parties conference is over, and comm shld promptly set about
                    preparation <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
